<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-29T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-29T22:00:00-05:00" n="1474" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1474">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.8571/5–3049: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-30T11:00:00+08:00">May 30,
                                    1949—11 a. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 30—5:11 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1887. Deptel 1081, May 28. Department will appreciate that I did not
                            expect publicity regarding my 1840, May 26, but did hope forwarding it,
                            particularly in plain language, might prove useful as it seems to have.
                            Could not explain at time in classified message due to overloaded
                            facilities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>